content: Nate Diaz is a professional mixed martial artist known for his time in the UFC. He has a reputation for his dynamic and exciting fighting style, incorporating elements of traditional martial arts and acrobatics. Diaz has a successful record of wins in the UFC, with the third highest number of bonus awards at 16. He was raised in Stockton, California and began training in martial arts with his brother at the age of 11. Before joining the UFC, Diaz competed in World Extreme Cagefighting, Strikeforce, and Pancrase.
